main event: A USAF aircraft crew sighted a yellow or amber colored object shaped like a Jack-O-lantern flying at 25,000 feet on February 11, 1955.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be flying at a speed of 1000 MPH,No maneuvering of the object was observed, The weather conditions were reported as good, The sighting was documented by an ex-military sergeant, The case was deemed to have insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: yellow or amber colored object shaped like Jack-O-lantern
